SIMPLE: lone
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lone
<hw>Lone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lane. See
<er>Loanin</er>.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lone</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lone
<hw>Lone</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Abbrev. fr. <ets>alone</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Being without a companion; being by one's self; also,
sad from lack of companionship; lonely; <as>as, a <ex>lone</ex> traveler
or watcher</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When I have on those pathless wilds a appeared,⟦br⟧
And the <qex>lone</qex> wanderer with my presence cheered.</q>
<rj><qau>Shenstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Single; unmarried, or in widowhood.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Queen Elizabeth being a <qex>lone</qex> woman.</q>
<rj><qau>Collection of Records (1642).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A hundred mark is a long one for a poor <qex>lone</qex> woman to
bear.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Being apart from other things of the kind; being by
itself; also, apart from human dwellings and resort; <as>as, a
<ex>lone</ex> house</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>lone</xex> isle.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By a <qex>lone</qex> well a <qex>lonelier</qex> column rears.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Unfrequented by human beings; solitary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus vanish scepters, coronets, and balls,⟦br⟧
And leave you on <qex>lone</qex> woods, or empty walls.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loneliness</ent>⟦br⟧
